  "steps": [
    {
      "order": 1,
      "instruction": "Peel or scrub the cucumbers (whichever you prefer) and cut them into 2 to 3 inch sticks. Put them into a large mixing bowl."
    },
    {
      "order": 2,
      "instruction": "Stir the rest of the ingredients (except the sesame seeds) in a small bowl to make the dressing."
    },
    {
      "order": 3,
      "instruction": "Drain any water that may have seeped out of the cucumbers and toss in the dressing. Once the cucumbers are coated, garnish with sesame seeds (if using) and serve immediately."
    },
    {
      "order": 4,
      "instruction": "When I made this today it was about 97 degrees outside, and I chilled the cucumbers for about 15 minutes in the fridge before tossing them together. I served the salad with a mildly sweet plum wine we bought while in Chengdu. The dish is light, cooling, and tasty!"
    }
